{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-1096","published":"2024-01-26T11:06:50Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:00.775184Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-22365"],"summary":"pam security update","details":"PAM (Pluggable Authentication Modules) is a system of libraries that handle the authentication tasks of applications (services) on the system.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA vulnerability was found in Linux PAM. An unprivileged user that is not yet in a corresponding mount namespace with ~/tmp mounted as a polyinstantiated dir can place a FIFO there, and a subsequent attempt to login as this user with `pam_namespace` configured will cause the `openat()` in `protect_dir()` to block the attempt, causing a local denial of service.(CVE-2024-22365)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"pam","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/pam&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.4.0-10.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["pam-debugsource-1.4.0-10.oe1.aarch64.rpm","pam-devel-1.4.0-10.oe1.aarch64.rpm","pam-1.4.0-10.oe1.aarch64.rpm","pam-debuginfo-1.4.0-10.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["pam-help-1.4.0-10.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["pam-1.4.0-10.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["pam-debugsource-1.4.0-10.oe1.x86_64.rpm","pam-debuginfo-1.4.0-10.oe1.x86_64.rpm","pam-devel-1.4.0-10.oe1.x86_64.rpm","pam-1.4.0-10.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2024-1096.json"}},{"package":{"name":"pam","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/pam&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.5.2-7.oe2203sp2"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["pam-1.5.2-7.oe2203.aarch64.rpm","pam-devel-1.5.2-7.oe2203.aarch64.rpm","pam-debugsource-1.5.2-7.oe2203.aarch64.rpm","pam-debuginfo-1.5.2-7.oe2203.aarch64.rpm","pam-debugsource-1.5.2-7.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","pam-1.5.2-7.oe2203sp1.aarch64.rpm","pam-debugi